  "text": "arices are most commonly noted in the esophagus and gastric fundus, and they may have ectopic locations such as duodenum, jejunum, ileum, colon, anorectum, retroperitoneum and rarely at the site of colostomy or ileostomy. Ectopic varices are an uncommon cause of gastrointestinal hemorrhage, but they account for up to 5% of all variceal bleedings [CITATION_1] .",
